	     Yaound - Four makeshift bombs exploded overnight in the main city in Cameroon's restive anglophone region, but without causing casualties, officials said on Monday. "Four home-made bombs exploded in Bamenda, one at 21:00 and the three others at 03:00," said a source close to the security services, reached from the capital Yaounde, adding "the blasts did not cause any casualties. They caused minor damage in the various places." A security source in Yaounde confirmed the account. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  